In his remarks at the AIPAC conference, Vice President Mike Pence reaffirmed the strong alliance between the United States and Israel. He emphasized that the friendship between the two countries has never been deeper, thanks to President Trump's leadership. Pence highlighted several promises that the President has kept, such as recognizing Jerusalem as the capital of Israel and supporting the country's security. He also criticized the Iran nuclear deal and stated that the US will withdraw from it unless it is fixed. Pence expressed his confidence in the future of Israel and the US, stating that the best days for both countries are yet to come.